  "title": "refactor(geo): remove support for position related options [PART-2]",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nThis PR removes the support of `enableGeolocationWithIP`, `position`, `radius` and `precision`. All those options could be replaced with the `Configure` widget. We don't need to re-invent the wheel, we can leverage the widget that are already present in the library.\r\n\r\nWe display a warning for `position`, `radius` and `precision` when the value provided for those options is defined. For `enableGeolocationWithIP` we **always** display a warning because the default value was `true`. In case the user rely on the default value we want to warn him but we also want to warn when a value is provided.\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n+ instantsearch.widgets.configure({\r\n+   aroundLatLngViaIP: true,\r\n+ });\r\n\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.geoSearch({\r\n    googleReference: window.google,\r\n-   enableGeolocationWithIP: true,\r\n    container,\r\n  });\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can take a look at the migration guide for more examples.",
